
[1]howitzer

   HOW'ITZER, n. A kind of mortar or short gun, mounted on a field
   carriage, and used for throwing shells. The difference between a mortar
   and a howitz is that the trunnions of a mortar are at the end, but
   those of a howitz are at the middle.
